column5: The Arkansas democratic party is not running any democratic candidate in the 2020 election so you should just assume that incumbent Tom Cotton will retain this seat

The Delaware Primary for both parties will be held Sept 15, 2020. On the democratic side, incumbent Chris Coons has a challenger: Jessica Scarane. There are a few people declared on the republican side but given this is a very same democratic seat, the real race is the democratic primary.

In addition to a normal senate seat up for election, there is a second special election for the other seat. The current occupant is appointed republican senator Kelly Loeffler. This special election will be held on Nov 3 but will be a jungle primary. That means that instead of party primaries, all candidates from both republican and democratic sides will be on the ballot. If anyone gets more than 50% of the votes, they're the next senator. If no one hits that limit, then there will be a runoff election on Jan 5th. Which is after we know the results of both the senate and presidential elections which makes that election potentially incredibly consequential.
Massachusetts is an incredibly safe senate seat but there's a competitive democratic challenge for incumbent Ed Markey's seat launched by house rep Joe Kennedy
The primaries for both parties is on Sept 8th and the current incumbent is democratic senator Jeanne Shaheen
